   (Easy to Understand) --> The Name of variable is stored in Stack Memory. 
          Stack memory is used for static memory allocation, where function calls and local variables are stored.

      Example --   X = 10

              X is name of variable. & X is stored in Stack Memory.


<|>  ğ‡ğğšğ© ğŒğğ¦ğ¨ğ«ğ²  <|>

     (Easy to Understand) --> The object of variable is stored in Heap Memory. 
             Heap memory is used for dynamic memory allocation, where objects and data structures are stored.

        Example --   X = 10

              10 is object of variable. & 10 is stored in Heap Memory.

